titles: The Well of Yourself | DAZED AND CONFUSED

texts.html: June 2, 2015 / emsnyder95

Well…what can I even say..? It’s been exactly 5 1/2 months since I’ve written a post or even had the urge to write. In fact, it’s been months since I’ve even done anything. I’ve been living in this funk and state of hazy confusion. Nothing seemed clear; everything fell apart.
text: Well…what can I even say..? It’s been exactly 5 1/2 months since I’ve written a post or even had the urge to write. In fact, it’s been months since I’ve even done anything. I’ve been living in this funk and state of hazy confusion. Nothing seemed clear; everything fell apart.

texts.html: Things are finally turning over. Life has started loving me again because I have started loving life. So many new things have happened in my life just really in the past few days. I’ve reconnected with the people I love, I’ve started renting an apartment with my best friend and for the first time in my life I have felt free without the guilt. I’m ready to live and love and find out everything about this world–the good and bad.
text: Things are finally turning over. Life has started loving me again because I have started loving life. So many new things have happened in my life just really in the past few days. I’ve reconnected with the people I love, I’ve started renting an apartment with my best friend and for the first time in my life I have felt free without the guilt. I’m ready to live and love and find out everything about this world–the good and bad.

texts.html: So, things are weird. My life is completely changing but I am totally fine with that happening. Whoever you are, wherever your life is right now, just hold on to the hope that things change. Everything can start over and become new. In the words of Charles Bukowski, “drink from the well of yourself and begin again.”
